tId\":\"a9e59ee791af10001\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01D4S9WcPvuqKyuax3AJer5K\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01SsWq8BHSF4cb31oaen7RHp\",\"uuid\":\"c8c047f5-982c-4dea-ad2d-737b2bd1bbc6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T22:10:00.281Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c8c047f5-982c-4dea-ad2d-737b2bd1bbc6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"726de64d-e8b7-4952-a516-72c4774b2003\",\"version\":\"2.1.62\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"ticklish-plotting-starfish\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01BN4wSJrVxFUntjyCjPTmms\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Entire CLI Hooks for Claude Code\\n     2→\\n     3→This document describes the hooks that Entire installs in Claude Code's `.claude/settings.json` to track AI-assisted development sessions.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Overview\\n     6→\\n     7→Entire integrates with Claude Code through six hooks that fire at different points during a session:\\n     8→\\n     9→| Hook                     | Trigger                        | Purpose                                        |\\n    10→| ------------------------ | ------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------- |\\n    11→| `SessionStart`           | New chat session begins        | Generate and persist Entire session ID         |\\n    12→| `UserPromptSubmit`       | User submits a prompt          | Capture pre-prompt state, check for conflicts  |\\n    13→| `Stop`                   | Claude finishes responding     | Create checkpoint with code + metadata         |\\n    14→| `PreToolUse[Task]`       | Subagent is about to start     | Capture pre-task state for diff computation    |\\n    15→| `PostToolUse[Task]`      | Subagent finishes              | Create final checkpoint for subagent work      |\\n    16→| `PostToolUse[TodoWrite]` | Subagent updates its todo list | Create incremental checkpoint if files changed |\\n    17→\\n    18→### Critical Capabilities\\n    19→\\n    20→  1. Prompt blocking - UserPromptSubmit hook needs to support returning a response to be shown in the cli session.\\n    21→    - Claude Code allows us to return a JSON response to stdout that can:\\n    22→      - Allow continuation: {\\\"continue\\\": true}\\n    23→      - Block with message: {\\\"continue\\\": false, \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"Your message here\\\"}\\n    24→  2. Transcript access - Hooks receive transcript path; system needs to read it for:\\n    25→    - Extracting user prompts\\n    26→    - Extracting modified files\\n    27→    - Generating summaries\\n    28→  3. Tool use ID tracking - For subagent checkpoints, need unique tool_use_id to correlate PreToolUse and PostToolUse events\\n    29→  4. Stdin parsing - Hook input comes as JSON on stdin; agent must define its input schema\\n    30→\\n    31→## Detailed Hook Info\\n    32→\\n    33→### `SessionStart`\\n    34→\\n    35→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code session-start`\\n    36→- **Handler**: `handleSessionStart()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:907`\\n    37→\\n    38→Fires when a new chat session begins in Claude Code.\\n    39→\\n    40→**What it does:**\\n    41→\\n    42→1.  **Parse Input**: Reads session details from Claude Code's hook payload (`session_id`, `session_ref`).\\n    43→2.  **Generate Entire Session ID**: Creates a date-prefixed identifier by combining today's date with the model's session ID (e.g., `2026-01-15-ab310c99-f579-4a12-8b3c-1234567890ab`).\\n    44→3.  **Persist Session ID**: Writes the Entire session ID to `.entire/current_session`. This file is read by subsequent hooks to maintain session context across hook invocations, even if the session spans midnight (date boundary).\\n    45→\\n    46→### `UserPromptSubmit`\\n    47→\\n    48→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code user-prompt-submit`\\n    49→- **Handler**: `captureInitialState()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:248`\\n    50→\\n    51→Fires every time the user submits a prompt. Prepares the repository state tracking _before_ Claude makes any changes.\\n    52→\\n    53→**What it does:**\\n    54→\\n    55→1.  **Concurrent Session Check**:\\n    56→\\n    57→    - Queries the strategy to check if another Entire session has uncommitted checkpoints on the same HEAD commit.\\n    58→    - If a conflict is found, outputs a JSON response that blocks the prompt and shows a warning to the user.\\n    59→    - The warning includes the other session's initial prompt (if available) and a resume command.\\n    60→    - Sets `ConcurrentWarningShown` flag in session state so the user can continue on the next prompt.\\n    61→    - Once the user commits their changes (or the conflict resolves), the flag is cleared automatically.\\n    62→\\n    63→2.  **Capture Pre-Prompt State**:\\n    64→\\n    65→    - Runs `git status` to get a list of all **untracked files** in the repository.\\n    66→    - Saves this list to `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json`.\\n    67→    - This baseline is compared later (in the `Stop` hook) to determine which files were newly created by Claude.\\n    68→    - Records the current transcript line count (`StepTranscriptStart`) for incremental token usage calculation.\\n    69→\\n    70→3.  **Initialize Session Strategy**:\\n    71→    - For strategies that implement `SessionInitializer`, calls `InitializeSession()`.\\n    72→    - **Manual-commit strategy**: Creates or validates the shadow branch (`entire/<HEAD-hash[:7]>`), saves session state to `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` with `BaseCommit`, `WorktreePath`, and `AgentType`.\\n    73→    - Handles shadow branch conflicts (from other worktrees) and session ID conflicts with appropriate error messages and recovery options.\\n    74→\\n    75→### `Stop`\\n    76→\\n    77→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code stop`\\n    78→- **Handler**: `commitWithMetadata()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:288`\\n    79→\\n    80→Fires when Claude finishes responding. Does **not** fire on user interrupt (Ctrl+C).\\n    81→\\n    82→**What it does:**\\n    83→\\n    84→1.  **Parse Transcript**:\\n    85→\\n    86→    - Reads the JSONL transcript from the path provided by Claude Code.\\n    87→    - Parses the full transcript. `CheckpointTranscriptStart` (or `StepTranscriptStart` from pre-prompt state) is used to detect whether new content exists since the last checkpoint.\\n    88→    - Extracts **modified files** by scanning for Write/Edit tool uses in the transcript.\\n    89→\\n    90→2.  **Extract and Save Metadata** (to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/`):\\n    91→\\n    92→    - `full.jsonl` - Copy of the complete transcript.\\n    93→    - `prompt.txt` - All user prompts from this interaction, separated by `---`.\\n    94→    - `summary.txt` - The last assistant message (used as checkpoint summary).\\n    95→    - `context.md` - Generated context file with commit message, session info, and file lists.\\n    96→\\n    97→3.  **Compute File Changes**:\\n    98→\\n    99→    - **Modified files**: Extracted from transcript (Write/Edit tool invocations).\\n   100→    - **New files**: Compare current untracked files against pre-prompt state to find files created by Claude.\\n   101→    - **Deleted files**: Query `git status` for tracked files that no longer exist.\\n   102→    - All paths are normalized relative to repo root (not cwd) to handle Claude running from subdirectories.\\n   103→\\n   104→4.  **Generate Commit Message**: Derives from the last user prompt, truncated and formatted appropriately.\\n   105→\\n   106→5.  **Calculate Token Usage**:\\n   107→\\n   108→    - Parses the transcript from `StepTranscriptStart` (captured at prompt start) to calculate tokens used in this turn.\\n   109→    - Extracts token counts from assistant messages: input tokens, cache creation/read tokens, output tokens.\\n   110→    - Deduplicates by message ID (streaming creates multiple rows per message; uses highest output_tokens).\\n   111→    - Finds spawned subagents by scanning for `agentId:` in Task tool results.\\n   112→    - Calculates subagent token usage from their transcript files (`agent-<id>.jsonl`).\\n   113→    - Aggregates into a `TokenUsage` struct with nested `SubagentTokens`.\\n   114→\\n   115→6.  **Invoke Strategy**:\\n   116→\\n   117→    - Builds a `SaveContext` with session ID, file lists, metadata paths, git author info, and token usage.\\n   118→    - Calls `strategy.SaveChanges(ctx)` to create the checkpoint.\\n   119→    - **Manual-commit**: Builds a git tree in-memory and commits to the shadow branch.\\n   120→    - Token usage is stored in `metadata.json` for later analysis and reporting.\\n   121→\\n   122→7.  **Update Session State**: Updates `CheckpointTranscriptStart` to track transcript position for detecting new content in future checkpoints.\\n   123→\\n   124→8.  **Cleanup**: Deletes the temporary `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<session-id>.json` file.\\n   125→\\n   126→### `PreToolUse[Task]`\\n   127→\\n   128→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code pre-task`\\n   129→- **Handler**: `handlePreTask()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:668`\\n   130→\\n   131→Fires just before a subagent (Task tool) begins execution. Captures the current state so that file changes can be computed when the task completes.\\n   132→\\n   133→**What it does:**\\n   134→\\n   135→1.  **Parse Input**: Extracts `tool_use_id`, `session_id`, `transcript_path`, and `tool_input` from the hook payload.\\n   136→\\n   137→2.  **Extract Subagent Info**: Parses `tool_input` to get:\\n   138→\\n   139→    - `subagent_type` - The type of subagent (e.g., \\\"Explore\\\", \\\"reviewer\\\", \\\"dev\\\").\\n   140→    - `description` - The task description (e.g., \\\"Find authentication files\\\").\\n   141→\\n   142→3.  **Capture Pre-Task State**:\\n   143→\\n   144→    - Runs `git status` to get current untracked files.\\n   145→    - Saves to `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n   146→    - This baseline is used by `PostToolUse[Task]` to determine which files the subagent created.\\n   147→    - **Note**: No checkpoint/commit is created at this stage. Commits are only created during task completion (`PostToolUse[Task]` or `PostToolUse[TodoWrite]`) and only if there are actual file changes.\\n   148→\\n   149→### `PostToolUse[Task]`\\n   150→\\n   151→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code post-task`\\n   152→- **Handler**: `handlePostTask()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:770`\\n   153→\\n   154→Fires after a subagent finishes its work. Creates the final checkpoint for the subagent's task.\\n   155→\\n   156→**What it does:**\\n   157→\\n   158→1.  **Parse Input**: Extracts `tool_use_id`, `agent_id` (from `tool_response.agentId`), `session_id`, `transcript_path`, and `tool_input`.\\n   159→\\n   160→2.  **Locate Subagent Transcript**:\\n   161→\\n   162→    - Constructs path: `<transcript_dir>/agent-<agent_id>.jsonl`.\\n   163→    - If the subagent transcript exists, uses it for file extraction; otherwise falls back to main transcript.\\n   164→\\n   165→3.  **Extract Modified Files**: Parses the transcript (subagent or main) to find Write/Edit tool invocations.\\n   166→\\n   167→4.  **Compute New Files**:\\n   168→\\n   169→    - Loads pre-task state from `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n   170→    - Compares current untracked files against the pre-task snapshot.\\n   171→    - Files that are now untracked but weren't before = files created by the subagent.\\n   172→\\n   173→5.  **Find Checkpoint UUID**: Scans the main transcript for any checkpoint UUID associated with this `tool_use_id` (used for rewind linking).\\n   174→\\n   175→6.  **Save Final Checkpoint**:\\n   176→\\n   177→    - Builds `TaskCheckpointContext` with all file changes, transcript paths, subagent info, and checkpoint UUID.\\n   178→    - Calls `strategy.SaveTaskCheckpoint(ctx)`.\\n   179→    - Creates a commit with the subagent's file changes and metadata including the subagent transcript.\\n   180→\\n   181→7.  **Cleanup**: Deletes `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tool-use-id>.json`.\\n   182→\\n   183→### `PostToolUse[TodoWrite]`\\n   184→\\n   185→- **Command**: `entire hooks claude-code post-todo`\\n   186→- **Handler**: `handlePostTodo()` in `hooks_claudecode_handlers.go:550`\\n   187→\\n   188→Fires whenever a subagent updates its todo list. Enables fine-grained, incremental checkpointing _during_ subagent execution.\\n   189→\\n   190→**What it does:**\\n   191→\\n   192→1.  **Subagent Context Check**:\\n   193→\\n   194→    - Looks for an active pre-task file (`.entire/tmp/pre-task-*.json`).\\n   195→    - If no pre-task file exists, this is a main agent `TodoWrite` - skip silently.\\n   196→    - This ensures incremental checkpoints only happen inside subagent Task tool invocations.\\n   197→\\n   198→2.  **Detect File Changes**:\\n   199→\\n   200→    - Calls `DetectFileChanges()` to check for modifications since the last checkpoint.\\n   201→    - Compares against git worktree status for modified, new, and deleted files.\\n   202→\\n   203→3.  **Skip if No Changes**: If no files have changed, logs a message and returns without creating a checkpoint.\\n   204→\\n   205→4.  **Extract Todo Content**:\\n   206→\\n   207→    - Parses the `tool_input.todos` array from the hook payload.\\n   208→    - Looks for the **last completed** todo item - this represents the work just finished.\\n   209→    - If no completed items (first TodoWrite), uses \\\"Planning: N todos\\\" format.\\n   210→    - This becomes the checkpoint description (e.g., \\\"Completed: Add user authentication endpoint\\\").\\n   211→\\n   212→5.  **Get Checkpoint Sequence**: Calls `GetNextCheckpointSequence()` to get an incrementing number for this task.\\n   213→\\n   214→6.  **Save Incremental Checkpoint**:\\n   215→    - Builds `TaskCheckpointContext` with `IsIncremental: true`, sequence number, and todo content.\\n   216→    - Calls `strategy.SaveTaskCheckpoint(ctx)`.\\n   217→    - Creates a small commit capturing the incremental progress.\\n   218→\\n   219→**Example sequence during a subagent Task:**\\n   220→\\n   221→```\\n   222→PreToolUse[Task]       → (no checkpoint - only captures pre-task state)\\n   223→PostToolUse[TodoWrite] → Checkpoint #1: \\\"Planning: 5 todos\\\" (if files changed)\\n   224→PostToolUse[TodoWrite] → Checkpoint #2: \\\"Completed: Create user model\\\"\\n   225→PostToolUse[TodoWrite] → Checkpoint #3: \\\"Completed: Add login endpoint\\\"\\n   226→PostToolUse[Task]      → Checkpoint #4: Final checkpoint with all changes\\n   227→```\\n   228→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"c2253736-3b07-4db4-b4d1-e8f984f777b8\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T22:10:00.285Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"Search the codebase for any documentation or code that indicates which agents support reading/displaying stdout from hooks. Specifically look for:\\n\\n1. Any docs about hook response formats in docs/architecture/ or similar\\n2. Any agent guide or integration checklist that mentions hook responses\\n3. Comments in the Gemini CLI, OpenCode, and Cursor agent code about hook output/response support\\n4. The agent-integration-checklist.md or agent-guide.md files mentioned in CLAUDE.md\\n\\nFocus on understanding which agents support displaying messages from hook stdout vs which ignore it entirely.\",\"agentId\":\"a9e59ee791af10001\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01D4S9WcPvuqKyuax3AJer5K\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01SsWq8BHSF4cb31oaen7RHp\",\"uuid\":\"6e728da4-1a8f-4344-adce-653766579811\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T22:10:00.490Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6e728da4-1a8f-4344-adce-653766579811\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"726de64d-e8b7-4952-a516-72c4774b2003\",\"version\":\"2.1.62\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factor